{
  "video_id": "Fb3yp4uJhq0",
  "title": "What happens when you have a disease doctors can't diagnose | Jennifer Brea",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 17415.0,
      "end_time": 19622.0,
      "text": "Hi."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 19622.0,
      "end_time": 20983.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20983.0,
      "end_time": 22704.0,
      "text": "[Jennifer Brea is sound-sensitive."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22704.0,
      "end_time": 25873.0,
      "text": "The live audience was asked to applaud ASL-style, in silence.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25873.0,
      "end_time": 29747.0,
      "text": "So, five years ago, this was me."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29747.0,
      "end_time": 31776.0,
      "text": "I was a PhD student at Harvard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31776.0,
      "end_time": 34472.0,
      "text": "and I loved to travel."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34472.0,
      "end_time": 39072.0,
      "text": "I had just gotten engaged to marry the love of my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39072.0,
      "end_time": 43071.0,
      "text": "I was 28, and like so many of us when we are in good health,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 43071.0,
      "end_time": 46477.0,
      "text": "I felt like I was invincible."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46477.0,
      "end_time": 50758.0,
      "text": "Then one day I had a fever of 104.7 degrees."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50758.0,
      "end_time": 52831.0,
      "text": "I probably should have gone to the doctor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 52831.0,
      "end_time": 55419.0,
      "text": "but I&#39;d never really been sick in my life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 55419.0,
      "end_time": 57796.0,
      "text": "and I knew that usually, if you have a virus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 57796.0,
      "end_time": 60953.0,
      "text": "you stay home and you make some chicken soup,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 60953.0,
      "end_time": 64499.0,
      "text": "and in a few days, everything will be fine."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64498.99999999999,
      "end_time": 67560.0,
      "text": "But this time it wasn&#39;t fine."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 67560.0,
      "end_time": 69121.0,
      "text": "After the fever broke,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 69121.0,
      "end_time": 73467.0,
      "text": "for three weeks I was so dizzy, I couldn&#39;t leave my house."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 73467.0,
      "end_time": 76335.0,
      "text": "I would walk straight into door frames."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 76335.0,
      "end_time": 80613.0,
      "text": "I had to hug the walls just to make it to the bathroom."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 80613.0,
      "end_time": 83825.0,
      "text": "That spring I got infection after infection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 83825.0,
      "end_time": 85676.0,
      "text": "and every time I went to the doctor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 85676.0,
      "end_time": 89533.0,
      "text": "he said there was absolutely nothing wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89533.0,
      "end_time": 91182.0,
      "text": "He had his laboratory tests,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 91182.0,
      "end_time": 93875.0,
      "text": "which always came back normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93875.0,
      "end_time": 95866.0,
      "text": "All I had were my symptoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 95866.0,
      "end_time": 97820.0,
      "text": "which I could describe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 97820.0,
      "end_time": 101370.0,
      "text": "but no one else can see."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101370.0,
      "end_time": 102617.0,
      "text": "I know it sounds silly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102617.0,
      "end_time": 105909.0,
      "text": "but you have to find a way to explain things like this to yourself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 105909.0,
      "end_time": 110114.0,
      "text": "and so I thought maybe I was just aging."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 110114.0,
      "end_time": 113691.0,
      "text": "Maybe this is what it&#39;s like to be on the other side of 25."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 113691.0,
      "end_time": 116808.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116808.0,
      "end_time": 119590.0,
      "text": "Then the neurological symptoms started."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 119590.0,
      "end_time": 124325.0,
      "text": "Sometimes I would find that I couldn&#39;t draw the right side of a circle."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 124325.0,
      "end_time": 130330.0,
      "text": "Other times I wouldn&#39;t be able to speak or move at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 130330.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132088.0,
      "text": "I saw every kind of specialist:"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 132088.0,
      "end_time": 135184.0,
      "text": "infectious disease doctors, dermatologists, endocrinologists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 135184.0,
      "end_time": 136945.0,
      "text": "cardiologists."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 136945.0,
      "end_time": 139679.0,
      "text": "I even saw a psychiatrist."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 139679.0,
      "end_time": 142947.0,
      "text": "My psychiatrist said, &quot;It&#39;s clear you&#39;re really sick,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 142947.0,
      "end_time": 146045.0,
      "text": "but not with anything psychiatric."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 146045.0,
      "end_time": 150094.0,
      "text": "I hope they can find out what&#39;s wrong with you.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 150094.0,
      "end_time": 154842.0,
      "text": "The next day, my neurologist diagnosed me with conversion disorder."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 154842.0,
      "end_time": 157255.0,
      "text": "He told me that everything --"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 157255.0,
      "end_time": 160916.0,
      "text": "the fevers, the sore throats, the sinus infection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 160916.0,
      "end_time": 164715.0,
      "text": "all of the gastrointestinal, neurological and cardiac symptoms --"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 164715.0,
      "end_time": 167457.0,
      "text": "were being caused by some distant emotional trauma"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 167457.0,
      "end_time": 170069.0,
      "text": "that I could not remember."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 170069.0,
      "end_time": 172546.0,
      "text": "The symptoms were real, he said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 172546.0,
      "end_time": 176527.0,
      "text": "but they had no biological cause."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 176527.0,
      "end_time": 179160.0,
      "text": "I was training to be a social scientist."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 179160.0,
      "end_time": 182416.0,
      "text": "I had studied statistics, probability theory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 182416.0,
      "end_time": 187058.0,
      "text": "mathematical modeling, experimental design."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 187058.0,
      "end_time": 191599.0,
      "text": "I felt like I couldn&#39;t just reject my neurologist&#39;s diagnosis."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 191599.0,
      "end_time": 193215.0,
      "text": "It didn&#39;t feel true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 193215.0,
      "end_time": 197356.0,
      "text": "but I knew from my training that the truth is often counterintuitive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 197356.0,
      "end_time": 200514.0,
      "text": "so easily obscured by what we want to believe."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 200514.0,
      "end_time": 205603.0,
      "text": "So I had to consider the possibility that he was right."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 205603.0,
      "end_time": 208919.0,
      "text": "That day, I ran a small experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 208919.0,
      "end_time": 213229.0,
      "text": "I walked back the two miles from my neurologist&#39;s office to my house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 213229.0,
      "end_time": 218475.0,
      "text": "my legs wrapped in this strange, almost electric kind of pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 218475.0,
      "end_time": 220102.0,
      "text": "I meditated on that pain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 220102.0,
      "end_time": 225320.0,
      "text": "contemplating how my mind could have possibly generated all this."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 225320.0,
      "end_time": 227219.0,
      "text": "As soon as I walked through the door,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 227219.0,
      "end_time": 228837.0,
      "text": "I collapsed."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 228837.0,
      "end_time": 232696.0,
      "text": "My brain and my spinal cord were burning."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 232696.0,
      "end_time": 237324.0,
      "text": "My neck was so stiff I couldn&#39;t touch my chin to my chest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 237324.0,
      "end_time": 239099.0,
      "text": "and the slightest sound --"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 239099.0,
      "end_time": 240958.0,
      "text": "the rustling of the sheets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 240958.0,
      "end_time": 243737.0,
      "text": "my husband walking barefoot in the next room --"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 243737.0,
      "end_time": 247832.0,
      "text": "could cause excruciating pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 247832.0,
      "end_time": 251235.0,
      "text": "I would spend most of the next two years in bed."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 251235.0,
      "end_time": 254939.0,
      "text": "How could my doctor have gotten it so wrong?"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 254939.0,
      "end_time": 257144.0,
      "text": "I thought I had a rare disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 257144.0,
      "end_time": 259926.0,
      "text": "something doctors had never seen."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 259926.0,
      "end_time": 261145.0,
      "text": "And then I went online"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 261144.99999999997,
      "end_time": 263980.0,
      "text": "and found thousands of people all over the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 263980.0,
      "end_time": 266087.0,
      "text": "living with the same symptoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 266087.0,
      "end_time": 267675.0,
      "text": "similarly isolated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 267675.0,
      "end_time": 269854.0,
      "text": "similarly disbelieved."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 269854.0,
      "end_time": 271161.0,
      "text": "Some could still work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 271161.0,
      "end_time": 273670.0,
      "text": "but had to spend their evenings and weekends in bed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 273670.0,
      "end_time": 276364.0,
      "text": "just so they could show up the next Monday."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 276364.0,
      "end_time": 278468.0,
      "text": "On the other end of the spectrum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 278468.0,
      "end_time": 280230.0,
      "text": "some were so sick"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 280230.0,
      "end_time": 282560.0,
      "text": "they had to live in complete darkness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 282560.0,
      "end_time": 285956.0,
      "text": "unable to tolerate the sound of a human voice"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 285956.0,
      "end_time": 289469.0,
      "text": "or the touch of a loved one."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 289469.0,
      "end_time": 294554.0,
      "text": "I was diagnosed with myalgic encephalomyelitis."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 294554.0,
      "end_time": 298987.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ve probably heard it called &quot;chronic fatigue syndrome.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 298987.0,
      "end_time": 300933.0,
      "text": "For decades, that&#39;s a name"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 300933.0,
      "end_time": 303578.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s meant that this"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 303578.0,
      "end_time": 304985.0,
      "text": "has been the dominant image"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 304985.0,
      "end_time": 309468.0,
      "text": "of a disease that can be as serious as this."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 309468.0,
      "end_time": 311016.0,
      "text": "The key symptom we all share"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 311016.0,
      "end_time": 315296.0,
      "text": "is that whenever we exert ourselves -- physically, mentally --"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 315296.0,
      "end_time": 317807.0,
      "text": "we pay and we pay hard."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 317807.0,
      "end_time": 321325.0,
      "text": "If my husband goes for a run, he might be sore for a couple of days."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 321325.0,
      "end_time": 325323.0,
      "text": "If I try to walk half a block, I might be bedridden for a week."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 325323.0,
      "end_time": 328261.0,
      "text": "It is a perfect custom prison."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 328261.0,
      "end_time": 331033.0,
      "text": "I know ballet dancers who can&#39;t dance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 331033.0,
      "end_time": 333230.0,
      "text": "accountants who can&#39;t add,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 333230.0,
      "end_time": 336421.0,
      "text": "medical students who never became doctors."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 336421.0,
      "end_time": 339056.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t matter what you once were;"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 339056.0,
      "end_time": 341475.0,
      "text": "you can&#39;t do it anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 341475.0,
      "end_time": 343389.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s been four years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 343389.0,
      "end_time": 346009.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve still never been as well as I was"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 346009.0,
      "end_time": 350683.0,
      "text": "the minute before I walked home from my neurologist&#39;s office."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 350683.0,
      "end_time": 353902.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s estimated that about 15 to 30 million people around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 353902.0,
      "end_time": 355604.0,
      "text": "have this disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 355604.0,
      "end_time": 358891.0,
      "text": "In the US, where I&#39;m from, it&#39;s about one million people."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 358891.0,
      "end_time": 363797.0,
      "text": "That makes it roughly twice as common as multiple sclerosis."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 363797.0,
      "end_time": 366563.0,
      "text": "Patients can live for decades with the physical function"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 366563.0,
      "end_time": 369310.0,
      "text": "of someone with congestive heart failure."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 369310.0,
      "end_time": 372927.0,
      "text": "Twenty-five percent of us are homebound or bedridden,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 372927.0,
      "end_time": 377385.0,
      "text": "and 75 to 85 percent of us can&#39;t even work part-time."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 377385.0,
      "end_time": 380064.0,
      "text": "Yet doctors do not treat us"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 380064.0,
      "end_time": 383116.0,
      "text": "and science does not study us."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 383116.0,
      "end_time": 387325.0,
      "text": "How could a disease this common and this devastating"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 387325.0,
      "end_time": 391264.0,
      "text": "have been forgotten by medicine?"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 391264.0,
      "end_time": 393812.0,
      "text": "When my doctor diagnosed me with conversion disorder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 393812.0,
      "end_time": 396524.0,
      "text": "he was invoking a lineage of ideas about women&#39;s bodies"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 396524.0,
      "end_time": 399215.0,
      "text": "that are over 2,500 years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 399215.0,
      "end_time": 400972.0,
      "text": "The Roman physician Galen thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 400972.0,
      "end_time": 403967.0,
      "text": "that hysteria was caused by sexual deprivation"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 403967.0,
      "end_time": 407125.0,
      "text": "in particularly passionate women."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 407125.0,
      "end_time": 409913.0,
      "text": "The Greeks thought the uterus would literally dry up"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 409913.0,
      "end_time": 412364.0,
      "text": "and wander around the body in search of moisture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 412364.0,
      "end_time": 414284.0,
      "text": "pressing on internal organs --"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 414284.0,
      "end_time": 416648.0,
      "text": "yes --"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 416648.0,
      "end_time": 419367.0,
      "text": "causing symptoms from extreme emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 419367.0,
      "end_time": 422715.0,
      "text": "to dizziness and paralysis."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 422715.0,
      "end_time": 426898.0,
      "text": "The cure was marriage and motherhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 426898.0,
      "end_time": 431482.0,
      "text": "These ideas went largely unchanged for several millennia until the 1880s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 431482.0,
      "end_time": 435764.0,
      "text": "when neurologists tried to modernize the theory of hysteria."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 435764.0,
      "end_time": 437441.0,
      "text": "Sigmund Freud developed a theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 437441.0,
      "end_time": 440261.0,
      "text": "that the unconscious mind could produce physical symptoms"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 440261.0,
      "end_time": 442300.0,
      "text": "when dealing with memories or emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 442300.0,
      "end_time": 444635.0,
      "text": "too painful for the conscious mind to handle."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 444635.0,
      "end_time": 449460.0,
      "text": "It converted these emotions into physical symptoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 449460.0,
      "end_time": 451680.0,
      "text": "This meant that men could now get hysteria,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 451680.0,
      "end_time": 455448.0,
      "text": "but of course women were still the most susceptible."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 455448.0,
      "end_time": 459089.0,
      "text": "When I began investigating the history of my own disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 459089.0,
      "end_time": 463011.0,
      "text": "I was amazed to find how deep these ideas still run."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 463011.0,
      "end_time": 464221.0,
      "text": "In 1934,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 464221.0,
      "end_time": 469020.0,
      "text": "198 doctors, nurses and staff at the Los Angeles County General Hospital"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 469020.0,
      "end_time": 470585.0,
      "text": "became seriously ill."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 470585.0,
      "end_time": 475020.0,
      "text": "They had muscle weakness, stiffness in the neck and back, fevers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 475020.0,
      "end_time": 478928.0,
      "text": "all of the same symptoms I had when I first got diagnosed."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 478928.0,
      "end_time": 482133.0,
      "text": "Doctors thought it was a new form of polio."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 482133.0,
      "end_time": 485088.0,
      "text": "Since then, there have been more than 70 outbreaks documented"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 485088.0,
      "end_time": 486273.0,
      "text": "around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 486273.0,
      "end_time": 489419.0,
      "text": "of a strikingly similar post-infectious disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 489419.0,
      "end_time": 493482.0,
      "text": "All of these outbreaks have tended to disproportionately affect women,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 493482.0,
      "end_time": 497433.0,
      "text": "and in time, when doctors failed to find the one cause of the disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 497433.0,
      "end_time": 501115.0,
      "text": "they thought that these outbreaks were mass hysteria."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 501115.0,
      "end_time": 505567.0,
      "text": "Why has this idea had such staying power?"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 505567.0,
      "end_time": 507387.0,
      "text": "I do think it has to do with sexism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 507387.0,
      "end_time": 510852.0,
      "text": "but I also think that fundamentally, doctors want to help."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 510852.0,
      "end_time": 512646.0,
      "text": "They want to know the answer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 512645.99999999994,
      "end_time": 517560.99999999994,
      "text": "and this category allows doctors to treat what would otherwise be untreatable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 517561.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521079.00000000006,
      "text": "to explain illnesses that have no explanation."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 521078.99999999994,
      "end_time": 524382.0,
      "text": "The problem is that this can cause real harm."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 524382.0,
      "end_time": 528002.0,
      "text": "In the 1950s, a psychiatrist named Eliot Slater"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 528002.0,
      "end_time": 532766.0,
      "text": "studied a cohort of 85 patients who had been diagnosed with hysteria."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 532766.0,
      "end_time": 536787.0,
      "text": "Nine years later, 12 of them were dead and 30 had become disabled."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 536787.0,
      "end_time": 540244.0,
      "text": "Many had undiagnosed conditions like multiple sclerosis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 540244.0,
      "end_time": 543259.0,
      "text": "epilepsy, brain tumors."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 543259.0,
      "end_time": 547563.0,
      "text": "In 1980, hysteria was officially renamed &quot;conversion disorder.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 547563.0,
      "end_time": 550911.0,
      "text": "When my neurologist gave me that diagnosis in 2012,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 550911.0,
      "end_time": 553552.0,
      "text": "he was echoing Freud&#39;s words verbatim,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 553552.0,
      "end_time": 554727.0,
      "text": "and even today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 554727.0,
      "end_time": 560487.0,
      "text": "women are 2 to 10 times more likely to receive that diagnosis."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 560487.0,
      "end_time": 564510.0,
      "text": "The problem with the theory of hysteria or psychogenic illness"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 564510.0,
      "end_time": 566568.0,
      "text": "is that it can never be proven."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 566568.0,
      "end_time": 570192.0,
      "text": "It is by definition the absence of evidence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 570192.0,
      "end_time": 571591.0,
      "text": "and in the case of ME,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 571591.0,
      "end_time": 575620.0,
      "text": "psychological explanations have held back biological research."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 575620.0,
      "end_time": 579321.0,
      "text": "All around the world, ME is one of the least funded diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 579321.0,
      "end_time": 586809.0,
      "text": "In the US, we spend each year roughly 2,500 dollars per AIDS patient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 586809.0,
      "end_time": 590100.0,
      "text": "250 dollars per MS patient"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 590100.0,
      "end_time": 594125.0,
      "text": "and just 5 dollars per year per ME patient."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 594125.0,
      "end_time": 596230.0,
      "text": "This was not just lightning."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 596230.0,
      "end_time": 598494.0,
      "text": "I was not just unlucky."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 598494.0,
      "end_time": 601609.0,
      "text": "The ignorance surrounding my disease has been a choice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 601609.0,
      "end_time": 607535.0,
      "text": "a choice made by the institutions that were supposed to protect us."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 607535.0,
      "end_time": 610430.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t know why ME sometimes runs in families,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 610430.0,
      "end_time": 612919.0,
      "text": "why you can get it after almost any infection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 612919.0,
      "end_time": 617123.0,
      "text": "from enteroviruses to Epstein-Barr virus to Q fever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 617123.0,
      "end_time": 621058.0,
      "text": "or why it affects women at two to three times the rate of men."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 621058.0,
      "end_time": 624356.0,
      "text": "This issue is much bigger than just my disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 624356.0,
      "end_time": 625563.0,
      "text": "When I first got sick,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 625563.0,
      "end_time": 628180.0,
      "text": "old friends were reaching out to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 628180.0,
      "end_time": 631333.0,
      "text": "I soon found myself a part of a cohort of women in their late 20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 631333.0,
      "end_time": 634012.0,
      "text": "whose bodies were falling apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 634012.0,
      "end_time": 636891.0,
      "text": "What was striking was just how much trouble we were having"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 636891.0,
      "end_time": 638577.0,
      "text": "being taken seriously."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 638577.0,
      "end_time": 640559.0,
      "text": "I learned of one woman with scleroderma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 640559.0,
      "end_time": 642683.0,
      "text": "an autoimmune connective tissue disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 642683.0,
      "end_time": 645417.0,
      "text": "who was told for years that it was all in her head."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 645417.0,
      "end_time": 647953.0,
      "text": "Between the time of onset and diagnosis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 647953.0,
      "end_time": 650404.0,
      "text": "her esophagus was so thoroughly damaged,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 650404.0,
      "end_time": 652673.0,
      "text": "she will never be able to eat again."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 652673.0,
      "end_time": 655376.0,
      "text": "Another woman with ovarian cancer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 655376.0,
      "end_time": 659188.0,
      "text": "who for years was told that it was just early menopause."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 659188.0,
      "end_time": 660780.0,
      "text": "A friend from college,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 660780.0,
      "end_time": 666222.0,
      "text": "whose brain tumor was misdiagnosed for years as anxiety."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 666222.0,
      "end_time": 669125.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s why this worries me:"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 669125.0,
      "end_time": 672600.0,
      "text": "since the 1950s, rates of many autoimmune diseases"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 672600.0,
      "end_time": 674818.0,
      "text": "have doubled to tripled."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 674818.0,
      "end_time": 677782.0,
      "text": "Forty-five percent of patients who are eventually diagnosed"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 677782.0,
      "end_time": 679800.0,
      "text": "with a recognized autoimmune disease"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 679800.0,
      "end_time": 682783.0,
      "text": "are initially told they&#39;re hypochondriacs."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 682783.0,
      "end_time": 685957.0,
      "text": "Like the hysteria of old, this has everything to do with gender"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 685957.0,
      "end_time": 688974.0,
      "text": "and with whose stories we believe."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 688974.0,
      "end_time": 692649.0,
      "text": "Seventy-five percent of autoimmune disease patients are women,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 692649.0,
      "end_time": 697076.0,
      "text": "and in some diseases, it&#39;s as high as 90 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 697076.0,
      "end_time": 699957.0,
      "text": "Even though these diseases disproportionately affect women,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 699957.0,
      "end_time": 701633.0,
      "text": "they are not women&#39;s diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 701633.0,
      "end_time": 705345.0,
      "text": "ME affects children and ME affects millions of men."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 705345.0,
      "end_time": 707154.0,
      "text": "And as one patient told me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 707154.0,
      "end_time": 708686.0,
      "text": "we get it coming and going --"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 708686.0,
      "end_time": 712318.0,
      "text": "if you&#39;re a woman, you&#39;re told you&#39;re exaggerating your symptoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 712318.0,
      "end_time": 716676.0,
      "text": "but if you&#39;re a guy, you&#39;re told to be strong, to buck up."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 716676.0,
      "end_time": 729419.0,
      "text": "And men may even have a more difficult time getting diagnosed."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 729419.0,
      "end_time": 745914.0,
      "text": "My brain is not what it used to be."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 745914.0,
      "end_time": 748645.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the good part:"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 748645.0,
      "end_time": 751903.0,
      "text": "despite everything, I still have hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 751903.0,
      "end_time": 755827.0,
      "text": "So many diseases were once thought of as psychological"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 755827.0,
      "end_time": 759323.0,
      "text": "until science uncovered their biological mechanisms."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 759323.0,
      "end_time": 762441.0,
      "text": "Patients with epilepsy could be forcibly institutionalized"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 762441.0,
      "end_time": 767500.0,
      "text": "until the EEG was able to measure abnormal electrical activity in the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 767500.0,
      "end_time": 771800.0,
      "text": "Multiple sclerosis could be misdiagnosed as hysterical paralysis"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 771800.0,
      "end_time": 775945.0,
      "text": "until the CAT scan and the MRI discovered brain lesions."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 775945.0,
      "end_time": 777484.0,
      "text": "And recently, we used to think"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 777484.0,
      "end_time": 780328.0,
      "text": "that stomach ulcers were just caused by stress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 780328.0,
      "end_time": 784801.0,
      "text": "until we discovered that H. pylori was the culprit."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 784801.0,
      "end_time": 787719.0,
      "text": "ME has never benefited from the kind of science"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 787719.0,
      "end_time": 790053.0,
      "text": "that other diseases have had,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 790053.0,
      "end_time": 792661.0,
      "text": "but that&#39;s starting to change."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 792661.0,
      "end_time": 796226.0,
      "text": "In Germany, scientists are starting to find evidence of autoimmunity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 796226.0,
      "end_time": 799406.0,
      "text": "and in Japan, of brain inflammation."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 799406.0,
      "end_time": 802484.0,
      "text": "In the US, scientists at Stanford are finding abnormalities"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 802484.0,
      "end_time": 804404.0,
      "text": "in energy metabolism"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 804404.0,
      "end_time": 808640.0,
      "text": "that are 16 standard deviations away from normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 808640.0,
      "end_time": 812709.0,
      "text": "And in Norway, researchers are running a phase-3 clinical trial"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 812709.0,
      "end_time": 817798.0,
      "text": "on a cancer drug that in some patients causes complete remission."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 817798.0,
      "end_time": 820316.0,
      "text": "What also gives me hope"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 820316.0,
      "end_time": 823968.0,
      "text": "is the resilience of patients."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 823968.0,
      "end_time": 826251.0,
      "text": "Online we came together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 826251.0,
      "end_time": 829449.0,
      "text": "and we shared our stories."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 829449.0,
      "end_time": 832743.0,
      "text": "We devoured what research there was."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 832743.0,
      "end_time": 835496.0,
      "text": "We experimented on ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 835496.0,
      "end_time": 837893.0,
      "text": "We became our own scientists and our own doctors"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 837893.0,
      "end_time": 840378.0,
      "text": "because we had to be."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 840378.0,
      "end_time": 844141.0,
      "text": "And slowly I added five percent here, five percent there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 844141.0,
      "end_time": 846398.0,
      "text": "until eventually, on a good day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 846398.0,
      "end_time": 849815.0,
      "text": "I was able to leave my home."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 849815.0,
      "end_time": 852568.0,
      "text": "I still had to make ridiculous choices:"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 852568.0,
      "end_time": 856924.0,
      "text": "Will I sit in the garden for 15 minutes, or will I wash my hair today?"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 856924.0,
      "end_time": 859693.0,
      "text": "But it gave me hope that I could be treated."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 859693.0,
      "end_time": 862789.0,
      "text": "I had a sick body; that was all."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 862789.0,
      "end_time": 867740.0,
      "text": "And with the right kind of help, maybe one day I could get better."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 867740.0,
      "end_time": 871466.0,
      "text": "I came together with patients around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 871466.0,
      "end_time": 873863.0,
      "text": "and we started to fight."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 873863.0,
      "end_time": 877698.0,
      "text": "We have filled the void with something wonderful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 877698.0,
      "end_time": 880662.0,
      "text": "but it is not enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 880662.0,
      "end_time": 884723.0,
      "text": "I still don&#39;t know if I will ever be able to run again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 884723.0,
      "end_time": 886644.0,
      "text": "or walk at any distance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 886644.0,
      "end_time": 891143.0,
      "text": "or do any of those kinetic things that I now only get to do in my dreams."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 891143.0,
      "end_time": 895955.0,
      "text": "But I am so grateful for how far I have come."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 895955.0,
      "end_time": 897464.0,
      "text": "Progress is slow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 897464.0,
      "end_time": 899310.0,
      "text": "and it is up"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 899310.0,
      "end_time": 901222.0,
      "text": "and it is down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 901222.0,
      "end_time": 906013.0,
      "text": "but I am getting a little better each day."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 906013.0,
      "end_time": 910548.0,
      "text": "I remember what it was like when I was stuck in that bedroom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 910548.0,
      "end_time": 915226.0,
      "text": "when it had been months since I had seen the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 915226.0,
      "end_time": 918961.0,
      "text": "I thought that I would die there."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 918961.0,
      "end_time": 921255.0,
      "text": "But here I am today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 921255.0,
      "end_time": 923513.0,
      "text": "with you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 923513.0,
      "end_time": 928606.0,
      "text": "and that is a miracle."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 928606.0,
      "end_time": 932377.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know what would have happened had I not been one of the lucky ones,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 932377.0,
      "end_time": 934995.0,
      "text": "had I gotten sick before the internet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 934995.0,
      "end_time": 937777.0,
      "text": "had I not found my community."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 937777.0,
      "end_time": 941028.0,
      "text": "I probably would have already taken my own life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 941028.0,
      "end_time": 944094.0,
      "text": "as so many others have done."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 944094.0,
      "end_time": 947957.0,
      "text": "How many lives could we have saved, decades ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 947957.0,
      "end_time": 950626.0,
      "text": "if we had asked the right questions?"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 950626.0,
      "end_time": 953592.0,
      "text": "How many lives could we save today"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 953592.0,
      "end_time": 957205.0,
      "text": "if we decide to make a real start?"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 957205.0,
      "end_time": 960881.0,
      "text": "Even once the true cause of my disease is discovered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 960881.0,
      "end_time": 964380.0,
      "text": "if we don&#39;t change our institutions and our culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 964380.0,
      "end_time": 967658.0,
      "text": "we will do this again to another disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 967658.0,
      "end_time": 969676.0,
      "text": "Living with this illness has taught me"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 969676.0,
      "end_time": 973153.0,
      "text": "that science and medicine are profoundly human endeavors."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 973153.0,
      "end_time": 975768.0,
      "text": "Doctors, scientists and policy makers"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 975768.0,
      "end_time": 979568.0,
      "text": "are not immune to the same biases"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 979568.0,
      "end_time": 983377.0,
      "text": "that affect all of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 983377.0,
      "end_time": 987119.0,
      "text": "We need to think in more nuanced ways about women&#39;s health."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 987119.0,
      "end_time": 991245.0,
      "text": "Our immune systems are just as much a battleground for equality"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 991245.0,
      "end_time": 993253.0,
      "text": "as the rest of our bodies."
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 993253.0,
      "end_time": 996542.0,
      "text": "We need to listen to patients&#39; stories,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 996542.0,
      "end_time": 1000024.0,
      "text": "and we need to be willing to say, &quot;I don&#39;t know.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 1000020.0,
      "end_time": 1003231.0,
      "text": "&quot;I don&#39;t know&quot; is a beautiful thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 1003230.0,
      "end_time": 1007360.0,
      "text": "&quot;I don&#39;t know&quot; is where discovery starts."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 1007360.0,
      "end_time": 1009442.0,
      "text": "And if we can do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 1009450.0,
      "end_time": 1013169.0,
      "text": "if we can approach the great vastness of all that we do not know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 1013170.0,
      "end_time": 1015146.0,
      "text": "and then, rather than fear uncertainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 1015140.0,
      "end_time": 1018340.0,
      "text": "maybe we can greet it with a sense of wonder."
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 1018340.0,
      "end_time": 1024094.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 1024099.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1034099.9999999999,
      "text": "Thank you."
    }
  ]
}